
Nodejs is OS independent. It can run on linux, window, mac etc.
Below are the steps for installation on Ubuntu machine.

1. Requirements:

Please install following packages/libraries on your machine.
-----------------------------
Package         Version
-----------------------------
nodejs          > v0.10.33
npm             > 1.4.28



Please install following npm package
------------------------------
npm package         Version                   
------------------------------
express             > 3.3.4
jade                > 1.7.0
mongodb             > 1.4.20


2. Installation.
    2.1 Install debian packages on ubuntu machine using apt-get.
        e.g.
        apt-get install nodejs
        apt-get install npm

    2.2 Install npm packages either locally or globally.
    
        Install npm package locally
           npm install <package_name>
           e.g.
           npm install express
           npm install jade.
           
           local packages are stored in current directory under folder named "node_modules".
           local packages are not available outside of current directory.

        Install npm package globally
           npm -g install <package_name>
           e.g.
           npm -g install express
           
           Global packages are stored in standard directory: /usr/lib/node_modules/
        
